title: CORROSION RESEARCH LABORATORIES‐12: MINISTRY OF SUPPLY OUTDOOR EXPOSURE STATION, GLASCOED, WALES Testing Paints by Outdoor Exposure: Part 2
items.abstract: <jats:p>The assessment of panels is one of the most difficult aspects of exposure testing. In this paper the authors outline the methods adopted by the Ministry of Supply at their testing station at Glascoed, in Wales. In the previous part of this article, which appeared in the June issue of CORROSION TECHNOLOGY, they described the selection and setting up of the site.</jats:p>
